The settee was owned by Lady Thelma Furness, Edward's girlfriend at the time, who introduced the pair during a party at her Burrough Court house in Leicestershire in 1931.

The Prince of Wales, Lady Furness and Simpson would often talk together on the then three-seater couch, according to Northamptonshire-based auctioneer Jonathan Humbert.

But when it was revealed the future king wanted to marry Simpson, Lady Furness cut up the sofa in revenge, he said.

Now the seat is to be sold by auctioneers J P Humbert on May 22.

Mr Humbert said: 'Every once in a while, something truly remarkable is offered for sale.

