'This really is the original "seat of love" where arguably the greatest love affair of the 20th century began.

'Nobody knew it at a time, but this settee was set to change the course of history.'

In 1934 Edward transferred his affections from Lady Furness to Simpson, who had recently divorced her husband Ernest after years of living 'beyond their means'.

Lady Thelma had been visiting New York with her family, and on discovering Edward and Wallis’s new relationship cut down the seat to two seats.

The sofa has been restored from the frame up and has been re-upholstered in period blush pink velvet.

